edu.stanford.nlp.ie.regexp

Class ChineseNumberSequenceClassifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.nlp.ie.AbstractSequenceClassifier<CoreLabel>
      • edu.stanford.nlp.ie.regexp.ChineseNumberSequenceClassifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<String,String>

    public class ChineseNumberSequenceClassifier
extends AbstractSequenceClassifier<CoreLabel>
    A simple rule-based classifier that detects NUMBERs in a sequence of Chinese tokens. This classifier mimics the behavior of NumberSequenceClassifier (without using SUTime) and works on Chinese sequence. TODO: An interface needs to be used to reuse code for NumberSequenceClassifier TODO: Ideally a Chinese version of SUTime needs to be used to provide more flexibility and accuracy.
    Author:
    Yuhao Zhang, Peng Qi
